@hesterbruikman @errorists I'm just reading the conversation in #core about this that I missed yesterday. I'm under the impression that we can measure activity in a certain Whisper topic/chat, and thus there is some room for imagination here. See Andrea's comment here: https://github.com/status-im/infra-misc/issues/26#issuecomment-540490325

Another means to make chat more active would be to [load the latest N number of messages](https://github.com/status-im/infra-misc/issues/26#issuecomment-540680112), rather than last 24 hours. 

Here's [a spreadsheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1ELSjIjLbVqzufMynpiyHXex-Rh2QfUSSEfS267IUl-c/edit#gid=0) where we can capture ideas related to our `make chat more enjoyable to use` objective. And one also for [fixing significant blockers](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1kRxxXC9GXOTmzhJMgKgrrMdSZHRHxaKf61QMroEoL_M/edit#gid=0), and [polishing UI](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1MHd7utDWWe_x27PvjfyX1RcTdMq-dy1p5VfXrwVDrkk/edit#gid=0).
